<div class="qna-content">
<p data-block-key="hfkar"><a href="https://www.fool.com/investing/stock-market/types-of-stocks/value-stocks/value-investing-guide/">Value investing</a> requires a lot of research. You&#x27;ll have to do your homework by going through many out-of-favor stocks to measure a company&#x27;s intrinsic value and comparing that to its current stock price. Often, you&#x27;ll have to look at dozens of companies before you find a single one that&#x27;s a true value stock.</p>
